
** Invoking other command files

  - *$HOME* environment variables are allowed in file names.

  - *@?/* references =$ORACLE_HOME/=

  - *@@* invokes the file in the interactive mode from the current
    working directory. in a command file it runs the file from the same
    directory as the command file.

** Qouting

   - = 'O''Reily' = '' quotes the single quote character. Another
     possibility is to use = chr(39) =.

** define

  - *define* displays the current defined and predefined variables.

  <example><verbatim>
  sql> define
  define _connect_identifier = "nine" (char)
  define _editor             = "gnuclient" (char)
  </verbatim></example>

** copy

  <example>
    SQL> copy from ops$maierh/maierh@nine to scott/tiger@nine 
         create test using select * from ops$maierh.test;
  </example>


** exec

  - Executes a single PL/SQL statement or a stored procedure. It's a
    synonym for 'begin <statement> end;/'.

** variable

  - Allows to create sqlplus bind variables. The variables can be set
    or used in PL/SQL. See also $IMPOS/sqlplus/test/var.sql

** ed

  - *ed* starts the editor.

** autotrace

  <example>
    sqlplus '/ as sysdba'
    SYSDBA> @?/sqlplus/admin/plustrce.sql
    SYSDBA> grant plustrace to ops$maierh;
  </example>

  <example>
    sqlplus 'scott/tiger'
    SQL> @?/rdbms/admin/utlxplan.sql
    SQL> set autotrace on
  </example>

** column

  - =heading=
  - =noprint=
  - =new_value=
  - =old_value=

** Other Commands

  - break on <col> [skip n|page]
  - clear screen  -- only in a terminal
  - clear columns -- reset all columns
  - clear buffer
  - title
  - btitle
  - repheader
  - repfooter
  - help index
  - help topics

** Options

  - /NOLOG needs a connect statement inside the script.

** Help

  - If help is not available it can be build with 'helpbld.sql'.

** Using of & ampersand

  - set define off
  - set define ^
  - set escape on
  - set escape off

** Compute

<example>
  SQL> break on report
  SQL> compute sum label "Summe" of byt on report
  SQL> select segment_name, segment_type, bytes /(1024*1024*1024) BYT 
       from user_segments order by 1;
</example>

** NEW_VALUE

<example>
define TS = "MM";
column TSS noprint new_value TSS;


select '&&TS' || '_RMS' TSS from dual;

create synonym abc for &TSS .abc;
drop synonym abc;
</example>
